                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Subcommittee of Five of the United Nations Disarmament Commission, consisting
                    of representatives of the United States, the Soviet Union, the United Kingdom,
                    France, and Canada, met in 19 sessions at Lancaster House, London, May 13–June
                    22, 1954. The Subcommittee Report and its nine annexes, consisting of proposals
                    and working papers submitted by the various delegations, is printed <pb
                        facs="0621" n="1435" xml:id="pg_1435"/> in Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 2, 1954, pages 177–183. Unpublished
                    documentation on the London Subcommittee meetings is in Department of State
                    files 330.13, 600.0012, and Disarmament files, lot 58 D 133,
                    “Telegrams–1954”.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
